2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 228
BY REPRESENTATIVE SCHLEGEL
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates May 5, 2026, as Literacy Day at the state
capitol and recognizes the Center for Literacy & Learning for its leadership in
advancing literacy statewide
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as Literacy Day at the Louisiana State Capitol and to
3 recognize the Center for Literacy & Learning for its leadership in advancing literacy
4 statewide.
5 WHEREAS, students who do not read proficiently by the end of third grade are four
6 times more likely to drop out of school, and those who lack basic reading proficiency are
7 nearly six times more likely to leave school without earning a diploma; and
8 WHEREAS, dyslexia is a learning disability that affects as many as one in five
9 individuals and presents a significant barrier to reading success without proper support; and
10 WHEREAS, literacy is foundational to a student's academic success, long-term
11 opportunity, and personal empowerment; and
12 WHEREAS, in 2022, seventy-two percent of Louisiana fourth grade students did not
13 read proficiently, and the state placed forty-second in the nation for fourth grade reading
14 achievement; and
15 WHEREAS, in 2024, Louisiana made historic progress by climbing twenty-six
16 places in national rankings to now rank sixteenth in the nation for fourth grade reading,
17 according to the National Assessment of Educational Progress; and
18 WHEREAS, the Center for Literacy & Learning was founded in 1992 and has spent
19 thirty-four years implementing evidence-based instructional and coaching practices that
20 improve teaching and increase student learning outcomes from birth to twelfth grade; and
