1 WHEREAS, the Center for Literacy & Learning draws on over three hundred fifty
2 combined years of professional education experience to focus on closing the achievement
3 gap through targeted, high-quality professional development for educators of at-risk
4 students; and
5 WHEREAS, the Center for Literacy & Learning employs a comprehensive literacy
6 wraparound approach, which provides services to educators, families, and communities that
7 support learning both inside and outside the classroom; and
8 WHEREAS, in 2019, the Center for Literacy & Learning successfully advocated for
9 the creation of the Early Literacy Commission; in 2024, it successfully pushed for the
10 establishment of the Louisiana Literacy Advisory Commission; both commissions are
11 instrumental in shaping literacy policies in the state; and
12 WHEREAS, the Center for Literacy & Learning, in partnership with the state
13 Department of Education, launched the Literacy Coaching Program in 2020; and
14 WHEREAS, in 2023, the Center for Literacy & Learning launched the Louisiana
15 Pilot Program for family engagement in literacy education; and
16 WHEREAS, improving literacy across Louisiana is vital to building a strong
17 workforce, creating high-quality jobs, and sustaining long-term economic growth.
18 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
19 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as Literacy Day at
20 the state capitol; does hereby commend the work of the Center for Literacy & Learning; and
21 does hereby celebrate the notable progress in fourth grade literacy scores in Louisiana.
